Chilean Stocks: Cap, Cencosud, CGE, Copec and Sigdo Koppers

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-16T20:57:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/chilean-stocks-cap-cencosud-cia-general-de-electricidad.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.8 percent to 4,215.44. Markets were
closed yesterday due to a local holiday.  Cap SA (CAP)   fell 1.6 percent to 19,200 pesos, the
biggest fall in a week.  Chile ’s largest iron miner and steel
producer fell in line with base metal prices, which retreated on
speculation that a moderating Chinese economy and sluggish U.S.
recovery may damp demand.  Other commodity producers also followed suit.  Empresas
Copec SA (COPEC)  , Chile’s largest pulp exporter, fell 3.7
percent to 7,390.1 pesos.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) increased 0.3 percent to 2,911.3
pesos.  Latin America ’s third-largest retailer by sales was
reiterated “outperform” at Credit Suisse AG, which cited the
company’s stable margins, according to a note to clients dated
yesterday.  Cia. General de Electricidad SA (CGE CC) advanced 3.4
percent to 2,640.7 pesos. The Chilean power holding company rose
after announcing Aug. 11 that its controlling shareholders
decided to end a pact that limited management’s ability to make
investments and take other actions without their consent.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   jumped 3.4 percent to 775.41
pesos, the biggest gain in five months. The holding company,
which has investments in industries ranging from automobile
sales to explosives, announced the creation of a new unit to be
called SK Internacional SA, which will handle its future
international investments, according to a filing posted on the
website of Chile’s securities regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
